# Transformerless AC to DC Converter PCB Design

## Overview

This project is a PCB design of a Transformerless AC to DC Converter developed using KiCad 10. The circuit converts AC input into regulated DC output using a capacitive dropper, bridge rectifier, filtering capacitors, and a voltage regulator.

The project was created to gain practical experience in schematic design, PCB layout, component placement, routing, ground plane implementation, and design verification.

---

## Features

* Transformerless AC to DC conversion
* Full-wave bridge rectifier using four diodes
* Capacitive dropper power supply design
* DC filtering using electrolytic capacitors
* Voltage regulation stage
* LED power indication
* Ground plane implementation
* Through-hole component design
* DRC verified PCB layout

---

## Components Used

* Terminal Block Connectors
* Capacitive Dropper Capacitor
* Bridge Rectifier Diodes (D1-D4)
* Filter Capacitors
* Resistors
* LED Indicator
* Voltage Regulator
* PCB Ground Plane

